OL,6,FIn a statement released at the time,
OL,7,FMay said it had been "an honour and a
OL,8,Fprivilege" to serve as an MP, and that
OL,9,Fshe would be supporting her successor
OL,10,Fto "secure a Conservative victory" in
OL,11,Fher Maidenhead seat.
OL,13,F'Hi, it's David Cameron'
OL,15,FNot to be upstaged, former prime
OL,16,Fminister Lord Cameron was also
OL,17,Fcaptured by a doorbell camera as he
OL,18,Fgave a helping hand to a separate
OL,19,FConservative candidate, ahead of
OL,20,Fpolling day.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/14
